From a2529e50a2bb9a6a8f096aa68c130413a398c488 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: poeggi <48416618+poeggi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 16:32:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 07/12] feat: add stable MAC-based UUID v5 to
 onvif_simple_server (GetEndpointReference)

- Add SHA-1 + get_mac_by_ifname + get_mac_by_ip + gen_uuid_v5_mac to utils.c/utils.h
- Compute device_uuid from MAC (RFC 4122 UUID v5) in conf.c after loading config
- Both legacy .conf and JSON config paths generate the UUID from service_ctx.ifs
- Falls back to random UUID if MAC is unavailable
- Add device_uuid field to service_context_t in onvif_simple_server.h
- Implement GetEndpointReference in device_service.c / device_service_files/
- Add GetEndpointReference dispatch in onvif_simple_server.c

Both wsd_simple_server and onvif_simple_server now derive the same stable device UUID
from the MAC address independently -- no IPC or shared state required.
